text: Färingsö or Svartsjölandet is an island in Sweden's Lake Mälaren. It covers an area of 82.02 km². The island is a part of Ekerö Municipality. The largest village on the island is Stenhamra. The island is also named after the village of Svartsjö. ==References== Category:Islands of Mälaren Category:Populated places in Ekerö Municipality Category:Uppland
